==English==

===Noun===
'''Aided Awareness'''  

# (Advertising) the percent of respondents who say they saw any advertisements for a specific product or brand in the past 30 days, in advertising research.
#:''Since respondents were asked specifically if they saw any of the company's ads in the '''aided awareness''' question, that score is higher than the one for unaided awareness.''

